x: There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the grove today. After they are done, there will be 21 trees. How many trees did the grove workers plant today?
If there are 3 cars in the parking lot and 2 more cars arrive, how many cars are in the parking lot?
Leah had 32 chocolates and her sister had 42. If they ate 35, how many pieces do they have left in total?
Jason had 20 lollipops. He gave Denny some lollipops. Now Jason has 12 lollipops. How many lollipops did Jason give to Denny?
Shawn has five toys. For Christmas, he got two toys each from his mom and dad. How many toys does he have now?
There were nine computers in the server room. Five more computers were installed each day, from monday to thursday. How many computers are now in the server room?
Michael had 58 golf balls. On tuesday, he lost 23 golf balls. On wednesday, he lost 2 more. How many golf balls did he have at the end of wednesday?
Olivia has $23. She bought five bagels for $3 each. How much money does she have left?
There were 7 fish in the aquarium. Later, the total number of fish in the aquarium increased to 13. How many fish were added?
A library used to have 300 books. After receiving a new shipment, the library's collection grew to 450 books. How many books did the libarary receive?
Maria had 10 stamps in her collection. After her birthday, she had a total of 28 stamps. How many stamps did she receive?
A parking lot had 25 cars parked in it. Later in the day, there were 47 cars in the parking lot. How many cars arrived during the day?
A farmer had 50 apple trees in his orchard. After planting more trees, he ended up with a total of 80 apple trees. How many trees did the farmer plant?
A bakery had 120 cookies in the morning. By the afternoon, they had baked more and had a total of 200 cookies. How many cookies was baked in the afternnon?
In a garden, there were originally 10 flowers. After planting more flowers, the total count of flowers increased to 18. How many flowers were planted?
Initially, there were 6 bicycles at the park. Later on, 4 more bicycles arrived. How many bicycles are in the park now?
Tom had 15 candies initially, while his brother Jerry had 25 candies. After sharing and eating 18 of them with friends, how many candies do they have now?
A basket contained 30 apples to begin with. After selling some at the farmers market, there were only 18 apples left in the basket. How many apples have been sold?
Samantha had 3 dolls. She received 2 dolls from her grandmother and 2 dolls from her aunt. How many dolls does she have now?
Initially, a school had 5 projectors. Over the past week, they received 3 projectors each day. How many projectors does the school have now?
z: There are 15 trees originally. Then there were 21 trees after some more were planted. So there must have been 21 - 15 = 6.
There are originally 3 cars. 2 more cars arrive. 3 + 2 = 5.
Originally, Leah had 32 chocolates. Her sister had 42. So in total they had 32 + 42 = 74. After eating 35, they had 74 - 35 = 39.
Jason started with 20 lollipops. Then he had 12 after giving some to Denny. So he gave Denny 20 - 12 = 8.
Shawn started with 5 toys. If he got 2 toys each from his mom and dad, then that is 4 more toys. 5 + 4 = 9.
There were originally 9 computers. For each of 4 days, 5 more computers were added. So 5 * 4 = 20 computers were added. 9 + 20 is 29.
Michael started with 58 golf balls. After losing 23 on tuesday, he had 58 - 23 = 35. After losing 2 more, he had 35 - 2 = 33 golf balls.
Olivia had 23 dollars. 5 bagels for 3 dollars each will be 5 x 3 = 15 dollars. So she has 23 - 15 dollars left. 23 - 15 is 8.
There were originally 7 fish in the aquarium. Later, the total number of fish in the aquarium increased to 13. Thus, 13 - 7 = 6 fish must have been added to the aquarium.
A library started with a collection of 300 books. After receiving a new shipment, the library's collection grew to 450 books. Therefore, 450 - 300 = 150 new books must have arrived.
Maria had 10 stamps in her collection. After her birthday, she had a total of 28 stamps. So, she must have received 28 - 10 = 18 stamps as gifts for her birthday.
A parking lot had 25 cars parked in it. Later in the day, there were 47 cars in the parking lot. Hence, 47 - 25 = 22 cars must have arrived and parked in the lot during that time.
A farmer had 50 apple trees in his orchard. After planting more trees, he ended up with a total of 80 apple trees. Thus, 80 - 50 = 30 new apple trees were planted by the farmer.
A bakery had 120 cookies in the morning. By the afternoon, they had baked more and had a total of 200 cookies. So, 200 - 120 = 80 cookies must have been baked in the afternoon.
In a garden, there were originally 10 flowers. After planting more flowers, the total count of flowers increased to 18. Thus, there must have been 18−10=8 flowers planted.
Initially, there were 6 bicycles at the park. Later on, 4 more bicycles arrived. Consequently, there were 6+4=10 bicycles in total.
Tom had 15 candies initially, while his brother Jerry had 25 candies. Together, they had 15+25=40 candies. After sharing and eating 18 of them with friends, they were left with 40−18=22 candies.
A basket contained 30 apples to begin with. After selling some at the farmers market, there were only 18 apples left in the basket. Therefore, 30−18=12 apples must have been sold.
Samantha had 3 dolls. She received 2 dolls from her grandmother and 2 dolls from her aunt, adding up to 2+2=4 more dolls. Now, Samantha has 3+4=7 dolls.
Initially, a school had 5 projectors. Over a week, they received 3 projectors each day, making it 3×7=21 projectors received in total. So, the school now has 5+21=26 projectors.
